                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13957096" author="bikassaha" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 22:31:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hitesh&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hitesh&quot;&gt;hitesh&lt;/a&gt; Please review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13957099" author="hitesh" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 22:34:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good. Should we be catching and ignoring any exceptions related to loggers ( or fail the container after the task completes in such cases)? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13957102" author="bikassaha" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 22:37:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The code fails containers on such exceptions after logging the exception. That seems the right approach for now to find issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13957105" author="bikassaha" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 22:42:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tassapola&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tassapola&quot;&gt;tassapola&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yeshavora&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yeshavora&quot;&gt;yeshavora&lt;/a&gt; for finding the issue via trying Tez on Windows. Windows is strict about open files and by default does not allow multiple writable opens for the same file. After completion of a task the standard out would be redirected back to existing stdout file which would try to open the stdout file with write permission. Since stdout was created by the NM launcher, some other process already has the file open with write permissions. So the new open would fail.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13957107" author="bikassaha" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 22:45:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch removes an unused method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13957144" author="bikassaha" created="Tue, 1 Apr 2014 23:30:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;commit 2e7086a004720624ba335a9b94b99629ec116456&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Bikas Saha &amp;lt;bikas@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   Tue Apr 1 16:29:20 2014 -0700&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TEZ-1009&quot; title=&quot;Fixes in log file roll-over&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TEZ-1009&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TEZ-1009&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Fixes in log file roll-over (bikas)&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for the reviews.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13965898" author="sseth" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2014 21:46:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think we should be creating _post files for task logs. A container is likely to be used far more often than the AM - and the number of files (even though just 1 more) adds up fast. Sequencing of logs on containers isn&apos;t too useful. Had specifically skipped doing this when the AM log changes were made.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13965910" author="bikassaha" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2014 21:55:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please feel free to make the change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14124004" author="bikassaha" created="Sat, 6 Sep 2014 01:35:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for jiras fixed in 0.5.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
